cisco was founded in 1984 by a small group of computer scientists from stanford university. since the company's inception, cisco engineers have been leaders in the development of internet protocol (ip)-based networking technologies. today, with more than 71,000 employees worldwide, this tradition of innovation continues with industry-leading products and solutions in the company's core development areas of routing and switching, as well as in advanced technologies such as home networking, ip telephony, optical networking, security, storage area networking, and wireless technology. in addition to its products, cisco provides a broad range of service offerings, including technical su
